fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.auth

Interface IUser

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ILocalized

    public interface IUser
extends ILocalized
    Represents an application user.

    The only required attributes are the principal (the user's unique login name within the scope of the associated directory service) and the active status. Optional attributes include the surname (last name, or family name), the given name (first name), the e-mail address, and preferences for the user's locale (language and country) and time zone.

    The user's credentials (in most common cases, a password) are not defined using this interface. Passwords are not always used or required (for example, when using client certificates or Single Sign-On) and may be implemented in different ways. It is therefore the responsability of authentication services to identify the user in an appropriate way. Implementations of IPlatformConnector do however provide simple access to their associated authentication services.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be safe for concurrent access.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    IDirectoryService.getUser(String), IPasswordAuthnService.authenticate(String, char[]), ITicket.getAuthenticatedUser()

      • getCommonName

        default String getCommonName()
        Gets the user's common name.

        This is an optional attribute

        The default implementation concatenates the givenName attribute with the surName attribute, if both are defined. If only one of these two attributes is defined, it will be returned as-is. If neither of these two attributes is defined, null is returned. Other implementations may override this default behavior.

        Returns:
        the user's common name, if defined, or null.
        Since:
        1.0
